DefaultReaderConfiguration.fullDescription: Collects events from FireEye Operating System.

file.toolTipText: Directory or path to read from

string.toolTipText: Hostname of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

integer.toolTipText: Port number of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

select.toolTipText: Data routing (normalized alerts to Manager and/or raw data to nDepth)

integer.toolTipText: Number of seconds between log reads

FastPattern.description: 3, ServiceInfo: system release with patch id
FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ \S+\[\d+\]: \[[^\]]+\]: FireEye system release with patch id: [\w.]+

FastField.defaultValue: feInit called for "$4" as uid=$5($6) gid=$7($8) groups=$9($10)

FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ [^\[]+\[\d+\]: \[\S+\]: [^:]+: no rule to check for rule_type:
\d+ [-\w.]+ [^:]+: [^:]+: (?:New security-contents detected|Security-content has been downloaded sucessfully)
\d+ [-\w.]+ \S+\[\d+\]: .*\[[^\]]+\]: Postfix Queue counts, hold: \d+ active: \d+ incoming: \d+ maildrop: \d+

FastPattern.description: 71, ServiceInfo: received signal, sent by pid
FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ \S+\[\d+\]: .*\[[^\]]+\]: libevent: received signal \d+ \(\S+\), sent by pid \d+

FastPattern.description: 72, ServiceInfo: Get hold queue cleanup count

FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ \S+\[\d+\]: .*\[[^\]]+\]: Finished hold queue cleanup count \d+ files older than \d+ minutes
\d+ [-\w.]+ bott_process\[\d+\]: .*\[[^\]]+\]: Bott process received signal after [\w ]+
\d+ [-\w.]+ bott_manager\[\d+\]: .*\[[^\]]+\]: BOTT manager received \d+ signal from \d+

FastPattern.description: 87, ServiceInfo: httpd: appliance is up to date
FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ httpd: \[[\w ]+\] appliance is up to date
\d+ [-\w.]+ manual_vacuum_tables\[\d+\]: \[\S+\]: Finished vacuum for [\w ]+ in [:\d]+ minutes

FastPattern.description: 100, ServiceInfo: mgmtd: Appliance sizing reload due to
101, ServiceInfo: mgmtd: Security content update event

FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ sysstatd: The SysStat service failed while trying to obtain the ethernet IP addresses

FastPattern.description: 113: ServiceWarning: content channel not available, file has no content
FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ (?:httpd:.+?content channel not available|sc-upload: file \S+ has no content)

FastPattern.description: 117: ServiceInfo: Client address trying to connect
FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ vtsd: Client address trying to connect is [-\w.]+

FastPattern.description: 121: ServiceInfo: hostd probing is done; starting hostd probing

FastPattern.pattern: \d+ [-\w.]+ httpd: httpd secure channel: (?:SSL connection is established with|connection closed to) [\d.]+
(?:sc-upload: Security content stats:|rt-stats\[\d+\]: There was an error \[) *$

FastPattern.description: NullAlert: heartbeat; smartd; cimslp; vobd; vmauthd; ImageConfigManager
